Package com.xtructure.xevolution.evolution

Classes that define the behavior of the evolution process.

          Description

Interface Summary
EvaluationStrategy<D,T> The EvaluationStrategy interface describes the method for evaluating genomes.
EvolutionExperiment<D,T>  
EvolutionObject The EvolutionObject interface describes the common methods used by all xevolution entities.
EvolutionStrategy<D,T> The EvolutionStrategy interface describes the methods used at the highest level of evolution.
ReproductionStrategy<D> The ReproductionStrategy interface describes the method which produces new child Genomes for a Population.
SurvivalFilter The SurvivalFilter interface describes the method for marking dead Genomes in a population.
